comments: Wembanyama (SAS) legally contests McCollum's (NOP) layup attempt.

Ingram (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Sochan (SAS) at the start of the drive. Vassell (SAS) attempts to release back to the perimeter and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Ingram, which causes Vassell to lose his balance.
Initially, Alvarado (NOP) cleanly dislodges the ball from Sochan (SAS) and then Ingram (NOP) reaches in and makes illegal contact with Sochan's arm after he regains control of the ball.
Williamson (NOP) establishes himself in Jones' (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wembanyama (SAS) legally contests and cleanly block Williamson's (NOP) layup attempt.
Vassell (SAS) slightly extends his leg toward McCollum's (NOP) path and marginal foot-to-foot contact occurs during the pick.
McCollum (NOP) moves alongside Jones' (SAS) path and makes clean contact with the ball to block the driving shot attempt.
McCollum (NOP) initiates contact with Jones' (SAS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Williamson (NOP) slightly extends his arms toward Jones' (SAS) path and marginal contact occurs as Jones moves over the pick.
McCollum (NOP) brings his arm toward Jones' (SAS) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of Jones' drive.
Jones (SAS) slightly extends his forearm to release from the marginal contact with McCollum (NOP) as they come together at the end of the drive.
McCollum (NOP) moves alongside Jones' (SAS) path and maintains a legal guarding position to absorb the incidental contact during the driving shot attempt.
Wembanyama (SAS) makes contact with the ball while it is still in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Ingram (NOP) makes contact with the ball while it is still in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Sochan (SAS) jumps alongside Williamson (NOP) with a forearm resting on his body and marginal contact occurs during his contest of the driving shot attempt.

Williamson (NOP) drifts toward Vassell's (SAS) already extended arm as Vassell is retracting it away from Williamson when marginal follow-through contact occurs with Williamson's head after he releases the driving shot attempt.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Ingram (NOP) and Jones (SAS) mutually engage with one another and marginal contact occurs when the screen is set.

Ingram (NOP) steps on Vassell's (SAS) foot during the screen, but is able to move through the marginal contact.  As he is engaging with Jones (SAS), Jones stumbles to the floor but not as a result of any illegal contact by Ingram.
Marshall (NOP) immediately slides his hand off of Wembanyama's (SAS) side and marginal contact occurs after Wembanyama slips the pick.
After Jones (SAS) goes to the ground, Williamson (NOP) inadvertently trips over him and incidental contact occurs.
Daniels (NOP) legally contests Vassell's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
